</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-2064_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-fec59190-e730-4dd0-a33f-209c3ddf7782"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In an increasingly diverse and interconnected world, the urgency for racial equality has never been greater. Race Equality Week serves as a powerful catalyst for change, uniting organisations, individuals, and global supporters to break down barriers in the workplace. With this year’s theme, <em>#EveryActionCounts</em>, the campaign emphasises that real progress comes from collective and individual efforts. As we explore the significance of Race Equality Week, we will also spotlight organisations taking meaningful action to drive awareness and lasting change.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-2125_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-2124_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-2092_">Why Race Equality Week matters?</h3><div class="sc-xyPcs kkQLtl pf-2123_ pf-icon-right" data-scroll-to-top="true" data-open-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3"><details class="sc-bwrGHU cpUCet pf-2106_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-hUTmjW ewCXhB pf-2094_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="112a3b2a-4b99-4d31-ae5d-c21bcfd3e79d" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Addressing a persistent problem</span></div></summary><div class="sc-kgbRcZ iWirwY pf-2105_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goaELH eFZwMt pf-2104_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-2622_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-2621_"><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-2620_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-eade4641-3f8a-4b22-b6d4-e3e5f4ad71ba"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Race Equality Week highlights the ongoing reality of racial inequality, particularly in the workplace. Shockingly, two in five Black, Asian, and Ethnic Minority colleagues experience racism at work, ranging from offensive jokes to outright harassment. With this year’s theme, <em>#EveryActionCounts</em>, the campaign reinforces that recognising these issues is just the first step; meaningful actions, both big and small, are essential to driving change.
</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-bwrGHU cpUCet pf-2122_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-hUTmjW ewCXhB pf-2108_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="e79dc948-57a3-46f7-843d-5acd779a3ff1" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Promoting inclusivity</span></div></summary><div class="sc-kgbRcZ iWirwY pf-2121_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goaELH eFZwMt pf-2120_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-2627_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-2626_"><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-2625_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-4b77af68-c7f8-48e5-8f30-747b723d84ff"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">True inclusivity requires more than just awareness - It demands action. Race Equality Week fosters open dialogue among diverse racial groups, helping to dismantle stereotypes, build empathy, and create workplaces where everyone feels valued. By taking intentional steps to listen, learn, and engage, we move closer to a genuinely inclusive society.
</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-bwrGHU cpUCet pf-2572_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-hUTmjW ewCXhB pf-2558_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="1e2c457d-4e6a-48d9-932b-07b6cdb77f16" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Advocating for change
</span></div></summary><div class="sc-kgbRcZ iWirwY pf-2571_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goaELH eFZwMt pf-2570_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-2632_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-2631_"><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-2630_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-cb34024f-1b4f-48d4-aa42-72e8ffb82be6"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Systemic change doesn’t happen without a collective effort.   <em>#EveryActionCounts</em> serves as a rallying cry for organisations and individuals to push for policy reforms that promote racial equity across all sectors - education, employment, healthcare, and criminal justice. By taking responsibility for change, we can create a lasting impact.

</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-bwrGHU cpUCet pf-2588_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-hUTmjW ewCXhB pf-2574_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="e409b857-275d-4837-97c4-57afbdceebd4" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Empowering marginalised communities
